## Stack Management

### Stack Allocation

| Task Type | Minimum Stack | Sizing Method |
|-----------|---------------|---------------|
| Idle task | 128 bytes | Fixed (minimal) |
| Sensor task | 512 bytes | Static analysis + 50% margin |
| Comms task | 1024 bytes | Static analysis + 50% margin |
| ISR stack | 256 bytes | Worst-case nesting analysis |

### Stack Monitoring

```c
/* Fill stack with known pattern at init */
void stack_paint(uint32_t *stack_base, size_t size_words) {
    for (size_t i = 0; i < size_words; i++) {
        stack_base[i] = 0xDEADBEEF;
    }
}

/* Check how much stack was used (high-water mark) */
size_t stack_used(const uint32_t *stack_base, size_t size_words) {
    size_t unused = 0;
    while (unused < size_words && stack_base[unused] == 0xDEADBEEF) {
        unused++;
    }
    return (size_words - unused) * sizeof(uint32_t);
}
```

### Stack Safety Checklist

- [ ] All stacks painted with sentinel at boot
- [ ] Stack high-water marks logged periodically (e.g., every 60 seconds)
- [ ] MPU guard regions configured below each stack
- [ ] RTOS stack overflow hook triggers system reset or safe state
- [ ] Maximum call depth verified with `-fstack-usage` compiler flag

