## Buffer Overflow Prevention

### Ring Buffer Pattern

```c
typedef struct {
    uint8_t *buf;
    size_t size;        /* must be power of 2 */
    volatile size_t head;
    volatile size_t tail;
} ring_buf_t;

static inline size_t ring_count(const ring_buf_t *r) {
    return (r->head - r->tail) & (r->size - 1);
}

static inline bool ring_put(ring_buf_t *r, uint8_t byte) {
    if (ring_count(r) >= r->size - 1) return false;
    r->buf[r->head & (r->size - 1)] = byte;
    r->head++;
    return true;
}
```

### Buffer Safety Rules

| Rule | Enforcement |
|------|-------------|
| All buffers have compile-time known size | `sizeof()` or `#define` |
| All copy operations use bounded variants | `strncpy`, `memcpy` with explicit length |
| No `sprintf` -- use `snprintf` only | Static analysis / grep |
| Array indices checked against bounds | Assert or explicit check |
| DMA transfer length <= buffer size | Validated before DMA start |

---

## Watchdog and Recovery

- [ ] Watchdog timer enabled with timeout matching worst-case task period
- [ ] Watchdog kick only in main loop (not in ISR -- detects main loop hang)
- [ ] RAM integrity check at boot (pattern write/read)
- [ ] Critical state stored in non-volatile memory for recovery after reset
- [ ] Brown-out detection configured to trigger orderly shutdown

---

## Diagnostic and Telemetry

| Metric | Collection Method | Frequency |
|--------|-------------------|-----------|
| Stack high-water marks | Stack painting | Every 60s |
| Pool utilization | Pool diagnostic API | Every 60s |
| Heap fragmentation (if heap used) | Heap walk | Every 300s |
| Total free RAM | Linker symbol arithmetic | At boot |
| Flash usage | Build output (.map file) | Each build |

---

## Verification Checklist

- [ ] `arm-none-eabi-size` output reviewed for each build
- [ ] `.map` file reviewed for unexpected growth
- [ ] Static analysis clean (no buffer overflow warnings)
- [ ] All pools tested at capacity (forced exhaustion test)
- [ ] 72-hour soak test with no memory growth
- [ ] Stack high-water marks have >= 30% remaining margin
